<title>UK: IBM unit sets $250 mln three-year Eurobond.</title>
<headline>IBM unit sets $250 mln three-year Eurobond.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following bond was announced by lead manager SBC Warburg.</p>
<p> BORROWER   IBM INTERNATIONAL FINANCE NV</p>
<p> AMT	  $250 MLN  COUPON     6.75	MATURITY    15.MAY.00</p>
<p> TYPE	 STRAIGHT  ISS PRICE  100.913   PAY DATE    15.MAY.97</p>
<p> FULL FEES  1.375     REOFFER    99.738    SPREAD	+15 BP</p>
<p> MOODY	A1	  LISTING    LONDON    PAY FREQ    ANNUAL</p>
<p> S&amp;P	  A	   DENOMS (K) 1-10-100  SALE LIMITS US/GB/NL</p>
<p> NEG PLG    YES	 CRS DEFLT  NO	  FORCE MAJ   IPMA 2</p>
<p> GOV LAW    ENGLISH   HOME CTRY  U.S.	TAX PROVS   STANDARD</p>
<p> MGT/UND    0.20	SELL CONC  1.175     PRAECIPUUM  NONE</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7658</p>
